## ğŸ“‹ What is a List?

A list is like a backpack where you store several things together.

```elixir
# List of fruits
fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"]

IO.inspect(fruits)
```

```elixir
# List of numbers
numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

IO.inspect(numbers)
```

```elixir
# List of colors
colors = ["red", "blue", "green", "yellow"]

IO.inspect(colors)
```

## ğŸ¨ Access Elements

```elixir
animals = ["dog", "cat", "bird", "fish"]

# The first
IO.puts("The first animal is: #{Enum.at(animals, 0)}")

# The second
IO.puts("The second animal is: #{Enum.at(animals, 1)}")

# The last
IO.puts("The last animal is: #{List.last(animals)}")
```

## ğŸŒˆ Create Color Patterns

```elixir
colors = ["red", "blue", "green", "yellow", "purple"]

html_colors =
  Enum.map(colors, fn color ->
    """
    <div style="background-color: #{color}; padding: 20px; margin: 5px; border-radius: 10px; color: white; font-weight: bold;">
      #{String.upcase(color)}
    </div>
    """
  end)
  |> Enum.join("")

Kino.Markdown.new(html_colors)
```

